---
title: Middle Eastern Chickpea Bowls with Savory Pistachio Rice & Garlicky White Sauce
description: We swoon for shawarma. For this veggie-centric spin, we swap the traditional spit-roasted meat for roasted chickpeas, onion, and tomatoes, but keep all the same aromatic, warming spices. It’s all served over ultra-flavorful, spiced basmati rice that’s studded with pistachios. If you’re anything like us, one of our favorite parts about shawarma is the sauce selection—and don’t worry, we didn’t skimp. Drizzle over hot sauce and a creamy, garlicky white sauce, then prepare to be totally bowled over.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/middle-eastern-chickpea-bowls-e8e542fc.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/middle-eastern-chickpea-bowls-5eb082c2ff8d2876ce4bf9a2-be70b39d.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/middle-eastern-chickpea-bowls-5eb082c2ff8d2876ce4bf9a2
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Middle East
nutrition:
  calories: 750 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 93 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 610 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 2
TBSP. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Roughly chop @pistachios{½%ounce}. Drain and
rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce can}; pat very dry with #paper towels{}. Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}.
Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

> Mince a few onion wedges until you have 4 TBSP for 4 servings.

Melt 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add minced onion, half
the garlic, half the pistachios (save the rest for serving), half the @shawarma spice blend{1%tablespoon}
(you'll use the rest in the next step), and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @basmati rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup @water{3/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a big
pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat.

> Use 2 TBSP butter, a medium pot, and 1 1/2 cups water for 4 servings.

Meanwhile, toss onion wedges, @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}, and chickpeas on a #baking sheet{}
with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, remaining shawarma spice, @pepper{}, and a few
pinches of salt.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until veggies are tender and lightly charred and
chickpeas are crispy, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> Divide everything between 2 baking sheets for 4 servings; roast on top and middle racks,
tossing veggies and swapping rack positions halfway through roasting.

> It's natural for chickpeas to pop a bit.

While veggies and chickpeas roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and
remaining garlic to taste. Season with salt. Stir in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture
reaches a drizzling consistency.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in 1 TBSP butter and half the cilantro. Season with salt and
pepper.

Once veggies and chickpeas are done, remove from oven and toss with lemon zest.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{}. Top with veggies and chickpeas. Drizzle with garlicky
white sauce and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste. Sprinkle with remaining pistachios and
cilantro. Top with lemon juice to taste; serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.